<subSubSection id="CAFB653AFFFAF12BFC880885D1C6AF85" box="[813,1254,916,943]" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="825E36B1FFFAF12BFC880885D1C6AF85" blockId="14.[811,1455,916,1358]" box="[813,1254,916,943]" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="B095EAA3FFFAF12BFC880885D1FFAF85" bold="true" box="[813,1247,916,943]" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">
* The type locality of 
<taxonomicName id="45E14D32FFFAF12BFBB10885D1FFAF85" baseAuthorityName="Bolivar" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[1044,1247,917,943]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Paracinipe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exarata">
<emphasis id="B095EAA3FFFAF12BFBB10885D1FFAF85" bold="true" box="[1044,1247,917,943]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">Paracinipe exarata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
,
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CAFB653AFFFAF12BFB4E0885D16CA964" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="825E36B1FFFAF12BFB4E0885D053A864" blockId="14.[811,1455,916,1358]" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">
i.e., Sidi Ifni, is located south of Agadir, where the species is relatively common up to the Oued Dra. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="E6704B40FFFAF12BFB0C08C5D658A825" author="Descamps &amp; Mounassif" firstAuthor="Descamps" journalOrPublisher="Acrida" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" pagination="247 - 303" part="1" refId="ref11331" refString="DESCAMPS M. &amp; MOUNASSIF M. 1972. - Le complexe Orchamus, Paracinipe, Acinipe et Pamphagus (Acridomorpha, Pamphagidae). Acrida 1: 247 - 303." title="Le complexe Orchamus, Paracinipe, Acinipe et Pamphagus (Acridomorpha, Pamphagidae)" type="journal article" year="1972">Descamps &amp; Mounassif (1972)</bibRefCitation>
, the southernmost locality documented for that species is Tarfaya, Hassi-Zhar. 
<bibRefCitation id="E6704B40FFFAF12BFBE90F05D1FDA805" author="Massa" box="[1100,1245,1044,1071]" firstAuthor="Massa" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" pagination="435 - 475" part="3700" refId="ref12694" refString="MASSA B. 2013. - Pamphagidae (Orthoptera: Caelifera) of North Africa: key to genera and the annotated check-list of species. Zootaxa 3700 (3): 435 - 475. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3700.3.7" title="Pamphagidae (Orthoptera: Caelifera) of North Africa: key to genera and the annotated check-list of species" type="journal article" year="2013">Massa (2013)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that the species ‘is distributed in the western area of Morocco’.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="825E36B1FFFAF12BFCE60F44D16CA964" blockId="14.[811,1455,916,1358]" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">
<bibRefCitation id="E6704B40FFFAF12BFCE60F44D164A845" author="Morales Agacino" box="[835,1092,1108,1135]" firstAuthor="Morales Agacino" journalOrPublisher="Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" pagination="310 - 339" part="20" publicationUrl="http://hdl.handle.net/10261/148685" refId="ref12923" refString="MORALES AGACINO E. 1945 a. - Algunos datos sobre orthopteroides del Sahara Occidental. Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia 20 (3 - 4): 310 - 339. http: // hdl. handle. net / 10261 / 148685" title="Algunos datos sobre orthopteroides del Sahara Occidental" type="journal article" year="1945" yearSuffix="a">Morales Agacino (1945a</bibRefCitation>
, b; 
<bibRefCitation id="E6704B40FFFAF12BFBCF0F44D18CA844" author="Morales Agacino" box="[1130,1196,1108,1134]" firstAuthor="Morales Agacino" journalOrPublisher="Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" pagination="241 - 283" part="23" publicationUrl="http://hdl.handle.net/10261/150020" refId="ref13011" refString="MORALES AGACINO E. 1947 a. - Notas sobre ortopteroides de Ifni y Sahara Espanol. Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia 23 (3): 241 - 283. http: // hdl. handle. net / 10261 / 150020" title="Notas sobre ortopteroides de Ifni y Sahara Espanol" type="journal article" year="1947" yearSuffix="a">1947a</bibRefCitation>
) listed this species in five localities hinterland from Genei Ali to Bu Kerch, extending the distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="45E14D32FFFAF12BFC510F85D176A884" baseAuthorityName="Bolivar" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[1012,1110,1173,1198]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Paracinipe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exarata">
<emphasis id="B095EAA3FFFAF12BFC510F85D176A884" box="[1012,1110,1173,1198]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">P. exarata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the south of Boujdour: Genei Ali = Jeneig Aali = Khenigat Al, 28°15’28”N, 10°37’09”W; Dora = Dawra, 27°25’14”N, 12°59’21”W; Aserifa = Asserfa, 26°19’00”N, 13°41’60”W; Imiricli Lebiad = Imirikli Labya, 25°30’00”N, 14°03’00”W; Bu Kerch = Boukarche, 24°55’16”N, 14°44’23”W.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
